[mypy-boto3-builder](https://github.com/youtype/mypy_boto3_builder) carefully generates type annotations for each service, patiently waiting for `aiobotocore` updates. it delivers drop-in type annotations for you and makes sure that: - all available `aiobotocore` services are covered. - each public class and method of every `aiobotocore` service gets valid type annotations extracted from `botocore` schemas. - type annotations include up-to-date documentation. - link to documentation is provided for every method. - code is processed by [black](https://github.com/psf/black) and [isort](https://github.com/pycqa/isort) for readability. ## what's new ### implemented features - fully type annotated `boto3`, `botocore`, `aiobotocore` and `aioboto3` libraries - `mypy`, `pyright`, documentation_summary: The HTML text is a PyPI (Python Package Index) project page for "types-aiobotocore-bedrock-agent" version 2.12.1, released on March 5, 2024. It provides type annotations for the aiobotocore service, specifically for AgentsforBedrock 2.12.1, generated with mypy-boto3-builder 7.23.2. The package aims to enhance development experience in IDEs like VSCode, PyCharm, Emacs, Sublime Text, and others by offering explicit type annotations, client annotations, paginator annotations, literals, and type definitions for better code completion and error detection. It requires Python version 3.8 or higher and is licensed under the MIT License. The project is maintained by Vlad Emelianov and supports various Python versions up to 3.13. Installation instructions, usage examples, and information on how to contribute or report issues are provided.
